        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Code verification acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Solver must demonstrate at least second-order spatial convergence on the Method of Manufactured Solutions (MMS) for the incompressible Navier-Stokes equations. Convergence order must be confirmed on at least three systematically refined grids with refinement ratio r ≥ 1.5. Iterative convergence must reach residuals below 1×10⁻⁶ for all transported quantities."
      },
      "rationale": "MMS verification was conducted on three hexahedral grids (0.8 M, 3.2 M, and 12.8 M cells, r = 2.0). Observed spatial convergence orders were 1.97 for velocity and 1.94 for pressure, confirming second-order accuracy. Iterative residuals reached 1×10⁻⁸ for all runs. The MMS solution was independently reproduced by a second analyst using the archived input deck, confirming reproducibility."
    },
    {
