        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Discretization error acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Grid Convergence Index (GCI) for the hemolysis index QoI must be less than 5% on the fine grid. Richardson extrapolation must be performed on at least three grids. The asymptotic range criterion (GCI_fine / r^p × GCI_coarse ≈ 1 within ±10%) must be satisfied."
      },
      "rationale": "Richardson extrapolation was performed on four grids (0.8 M, 3.2 M, 12.8 M, and 51.2 M cells). The GCI on the 12.8 M production grid is 2.1% for the hemolysis index QoI and 1.8% for the area-averaged wall shear stress. The asymptotic range ratio is 0.98, confirming the solution is in the asymptotic convergence regime. The achieved level of 5 reflects the additional fourth-grid confirmation and the sub-3% GCI result at the production resolution."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/cou2/test-conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
