        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Output comparison acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Predicted hemolysis index (IH) must agree with measured values within the combined simulation and experimental uncertainty interval at all five operating points. Normalised RMS error across operating points must be ≤10%. Velocity field comparison against PIV data must yield average relative error ≤8% across all measurement planes."
      },
      "rationale": "At all five operating points the predicted IH lies within the 95% combined uncertainty band (simulation U95 from Monte Carlo + experimental U95 from repeat testing). Normalised RMS error for IH is 6.3%. Velocity field comparison against PIV data yields an average relative error of 5.8% across three measurement planes, satisfying both criteria. Bland-Altman analysis confirms no systematic bias in the hemolysis predictions."
    },
    {
