        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "QoI relevance acceptance criteria",
        "description": "The primary validation QoI (hemolysis index IH) must be the same quantity used in the regulatory submission. Secondary QoIs (velocity field, wall shear stress distribution) must be mechanistically linked to the primary QoI through the hemolysis damage model. The mapping from simulation output to clinical endpoint (plasma-free haemoglobin rise) must be documented."
      },
      "rationale": "The hemolysis index IH computed from the power-law damage accumulation model is identical to the QoI reported in the 510(k) submission. The mechanistic chain from CFD-predicted shear stress and exposure time through the Giersiepen–Wurzinger model to IH is fully documented in the model description report. A supplemental memo maps IH to expected plasma-free haemoglobin rise using published clinical correlations, closing the link to the clinical endpoint."
    },
    {
