      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/cou2/use-error",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Use error acceptance criteria",
        "description": "A documented simulation execution procedure (SEP) must be followed for all production runs. An independent analyst must reproduce the primary result (IH at the 5 L/min design point) within 1% using only the archived inputs and the SEP. Analyst qualifications must be on file."
      },
      "rationale": "A formal SEP was written, reviewed, and approved prior to production runs. An independent CFD analyst (credentials on file, 8 years rotary-pump CFD experience) executed the 5 L/min case from archived inputs and obtained IH within 0.4% of the primary result, satisfying the 1% reproducibility criterion. Deviations from the SEP are tracked in a deviation log; zero deviations were recorded for the COU2 production runs."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/cou2/model-form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/cou2/model-form",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model form acceptance criteria",
        "description": "The turbulence model selection must be justified by comparison against at least two candidate models on the FDA pump benchmark. The hemolysis damage model must be validated against published erythrocyte fragility data. Model form uncertainty must be quantified and included in the total uncertainty budget."
      },
      "rationale": "Three turbulence models (k-ω SST, realizable k-ε, and RSM) were compared against FDA PIV data on the benchmark pump. k-ω SST yielded the lowest velocity RMS error (5.8%) and was selected. The Giersiepen–Wurzinger hemolysis model was validated against published erythrocyte fragility data from three independent laboratories, with model predictions within the inter-laboratory scatter band. Model form uncertainty (±12% on IH) is included in the Monte Carlo total uncertainty budget."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/cou2/model-inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/cou2/model-inputs",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model inputs acceptance criteria",
        "description": "All uncertain model inputs (fluid viscosity, density, hemolysis model coefficients, boundary condition values) must have documented probability distributions derived from measurement data or published literature. Input uncertainty must be propagated through Monte Carlo sampling with at least 1000 samples. Input sensitivity indices must be reported."
      },
      "rationale": "Seven uncertain inputs were identified: fluid viscosity (normal, μ=3.5, σ=0.1 mPa·s), fluid density (normal, μ=1050, σ=5 kg/m³), inlet flow rate (normal, ±1% of nominal), outlet pressure (uniform, ±0.5 mmHg), and three Giersiepen–Wurzinger coefficients (log-normal, based on published inter-study variability). Monte Carlo propagation used 2000 Latin Hypercube samples. First-order Sobol sensitivity indices confirm the hemolysis model coefficients account for 68% of output variance, flagging them as priority inputs for future experimental refinement."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/cou2/test-samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
