      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/cou2/equivalency-input-parameters",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Equivalency of input parameters acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Simulation boundary conditions must be set to the experimentally measured values (not nominal values) for the primary validation comparisons. Any differences between simulation inputs and experimental conditions must be quantified and their effect on the QoI estimated. Equivalency must be demonstrated for all five operating points."
      },
      "rationale": "For each of the five operating points, simulation boundary conditions were set to the time-averaged measured values from the experimental run (not nominal set-points). Differences between measured and nominal conditions were at most 0.8% for flow rate and 0.3 mmHg for pressure. A sensitivity study confirmed these differences change predicted IH by less than 0.5%, which is negligible relative to the total uncertainty budget. Full equivalency tables are provided in the validation report Appendix C."
